Description: Shell small, conical, white or yellowish with convex, evenly rounded whorls divided by deep suture ( Figs. 1 A, C, E , 2A ). Shell surface with fine, frequent (8–11 on body whorl), spiral ribs, almost semicircular in section, divided by very narrow interspaces (
Fig. 2I
). Axial sculpture, except for straight growth-lines ( Fig. 2A, I ) absent. Embryonic shell intorted, of type B, partially eroded on studied specimens, smooth or with very low pattern of spiral sculpture ( Fig. 2G ). Aperture oval with acute angle in upper part, no teeth or folds on columella. Umbilicus clearly visible, narrow. Operculum transparent, without peg ( Fig. 2E ).
